                  <list>
                    <item>
                      <p>Vellum, about 10 3/4 in. by 8 5/8. This volume is palimpsest throughout (see <bibl>Add MS 14,623, upper text<ptr target="http://syriaca.org/manuscript/1512"/></bibl>), 
                      and the miserable monk <persName>Aaron</persName> deserves the execration of every theologian
                       and Syriac scholar, for having destroyed a manuscript of the <origDate calendar="Gregorian" notBefore="0500" notAfter="0600">vith cent.</origDate>,
                       written in three columns, containing works of Ephraim, some of which are
                       as yet unedited. Fortunately a portion of it (nineteen leaves) escaped his
                       ruthless hands, and now forms a part of <bibl>Add. 14,574<ptr target="http://syriaca.org/manuscript/307"/></bibl> (see no. <bibl>DXXXV<ptr target="http://syriaca.org/manuscript/308"/></bibl>.).</p>
